    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-01T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.942/622: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-01T14:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 1, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 2—7:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>772. Department’s 329, August 29, 8 p.m. In justice to Mr. Matsuoka<note n="30"
                        xml:id="d677fn30">Yosuke Matsuoka, Japanese Minister for Foreign Affairs
                        since July 22.</note> it should be emphasized that he had labeled his
                    remarks as “off the record”, as stated in my despatch, that he was therefore not
                    attempting precise phraseology, and that from the context of his remarks it was
                    clear that the “blow” to which he referred was not the actual abrogation of the
                    commercial treaty of 1911 but our notification of intent to abrogate.</p>
                <p>The facts and views presented by the Department will be carefully observed in
                    future pertinent conversation.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Chungking, Peiping and Tsingtao for Commander
                    in Chief.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
